                        "There are no problems with UK housing",
                        "Housing is perfectly distributed"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "The housing example asks about 'actors, institutions and power'. What does this mean?",
                    options: [
                        "Which celebrities own property",
                        "Who is building housing and what power do they have in the market",
                        "How strong construction workers are",
                        "Which politicians live where"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            title: "Important Economic Concepts",
            questions: [
                {
                    question: "What does 'scarcity' mean in economics?",
                    options: [
                        "When shops run out of products",
                        "Resources are limited relative to wants",
                        "When things are expensive",
                        "When there's a shortage"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "What is an opportunity cost?",
                    options: [
                        "The cost of a business opportunity",
                        "What you give up when making a choice",
                        "The price of goods",
                        "A discount on products"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "What is the difference between positive and normative economics?",
                    options: [
                        "Positive is optimistic, normative is pessimistic",
                        "Positive describes what is, normative prescribes what should be",
                        "Positive is good news, normative is bad news",
                        "There is no difference"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "What are incentives in economics?",
                    options: [
                        "Only financial rewards",
                        "Things that motivate behavior",
                        "Company bonuses",
                        "Tax breaks only"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "What is a perverse incentive?",
                    options: [
                        "An illegal payment",
                        "An incentive that produces unintended negative consequences",
                        "A very large bonus",
                        "An incentive for bad behavior only"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            title: "Microeconomics",
            questions: [
                {
                    question: "What does microeconomics study?",
                    options: [
                        "The economy as a whole",
                        "Individual actors like producers, consumers, and workers",
                        "Only small businesses",
                        "Microscopic organisms"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "Which of these is a topic in microeconomics?",
                    options: [
                        "National inflation rates",
                        "How firms decide what to produce",
                        "Total GDP of a country",
                        "National unemployment rates"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "Microeconomics studies consumers. Who can be consumers?",
                    options: [
                        "Only individual people",
                        "Individuals, firms, governmental and non-governmental organizations",
                        "Only households",
                        "Only businesses"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "What role do governments play in microeconomics?",
                    options: [
                        "They don't appear in microeconomics",
                        "Regulation and control",
                        "Only taxation",
                        "Only spending"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                },
                {
                    question: "Microeconomics examines distribution and exchange. This includes:",
                    options: [
                        "Only market mechanisms",
                        "Both market and non-market mechanisms",
                        "Only government distribution",
                        "Only private sector exchanges"
                    ],
                    correct: 1
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            title: "Macroeconomics",
            questions: [
                {
                    question: "What does macroeconomics study?",
